CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1958, page 11, reads: "Staunch Supporters - Among the staunch supporters of the United Negro College Fund campaign, who attended the dinner meeting Friday night, were left to right: Judge Homer S. Brown, Mrs. Leila Payne, Mrs. George Winstead and William Hardy, president of the Pittsburgh Tuskegee Alumni Association. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Judge Homer S. Brown, Leila Payne, Mrs. George Winstead, and president of Pittsburgh Tuskegee Alumni Association William Hardy, gathered for 1958-59 United Negro College Fund campaign at Greene Hearth
